        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:28PM CDT by NWS New Orleans LA</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Magnolia, or 10 miles south of Mccomb, moving
northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mccomb, Magnolia, Summit, Osyka, Smithdale, and Mccomb Airport.

This includes Interstate 55 in Mississippi between mile markers 1 and
23.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
